stylometry: The safety stock concept is that of having an inventory cushion in lead time to prevent stock out from when an order is placed and when it is received. The goal is to minimize inventory but not run out. Essentially the biggest variable is that demand in unknown. You must find the balance between demand and inventory to help determine safety stock. Other variables you must consider are costs - holding costs of inventory, etc. Keeping the goal in mind will help a company determine how much inventory to have in order to cover demand but still have backup.
